Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
This trailer looks very promising. Ultron's very creepy, especially when he walks into the room where the Avengers are just chilling and mangles the Patriot armor. But I had some issues on the first Avengers. There are my OPINIONS. I don't want to spark a huge debate on why I personally didn't like it. Plot holes, plot issues, and character issues. Examples of each include:

~Plot holes: (1) Nick Fury holding the Tesseract with his bare hands (2) When everyone is supposed to have a moment where they're all vulnerable and Thor looses his powers for some reason and gets it back suddenly but that isn't explained.

~Plot Issues: I'm not too keen on Loki being the main villain for the Avengers. There was barely any backstory on the Chitauri and why would Loki, a GOD, use ALIENS for his army? Why not monsters or something? The way they mixed sci-fi and magic together wasn't the best way of bringing them both together imo, and Captain America was a grumpy dick. That one scene where they're having a dumb child's arguement and nobody, not even the most maturest characters (Black Widow & Nick Fury) thought of breaking it up? They just joined in so that someone could conveniently blow up part of the Helicarrier!

~Character Issues: The dumb arguement between the characters, Cap being a dick, etc.

These are just my opinions on the 1st Avengers. I don't want to spark a 100+ comment thread about my OPINIONS. I have hope for Avengers 2 and am looking forward for that Hulk vs Iron Man scene ;)

I have a feeling, i might be wrong, but i think a few people are going to watch this. I know it sounds crazy but people should go watch this becouse of the effort they have put in this. They cant afford anything so they have to cope with a budget that is less than they deserve. Actors arent the best but they have passion in what they do. And even though the first avenger movie was a complete failure we have to appreciate the effort... Its not gonna be a box office hit that's for sure, but we can help them make some profit if we truly try our best. And its noble that they try to entertain people and whether they succeed or not we will be proud of them and appreciate the try.
And i have a feeling that this is not the last time we hear the name "Scarlett Johansson" again. She has hidden talent there and when she unleashes all, we will see great things in the future for her. Her looks arent that bad either and her body needs some work but she'll get there with enough strength and determination!

This looks terrible.  Where's Jocasta?  The Bride of Ultron?
See, Avenger's 162, comic book.  I think I would rather read that
again, then watch this movie, which looks like another ode to
"terrorists attach NY - Avengers asemble"... Yawn... Like watching
a football game, really... And what is with the giant Iron Man suit..
Like that is going to stop the Hulk, anymore than small Iron Man
suit could?... Or maybe this will be like the comic book, where it is
revealed that he comes to search for a bride, a human female, to
place in a cybernetic body (albeit, unwillingly)?... In the comic book,
the monster chose Pym's (the Yellow Jacket) wife, the Wasp, if I
remember correctly... He had the body constructed... all he needed
was a soul, or spirit ... Crazy guy, Ultron.
.. And why they not have secret identities anymore?
I mean, all Ultron has to do is find a girlfriend, or wife, hold
her hostage... But I guess these guys would say, "Eh, we don't
negotiate with terrorists..."
Who are they making this movie for?

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment: This really had me on the edge, especially after seeing Captain America's shield broken. Not even Thor, a god, a supreme being, could break it, so I wonder what in the name of fondue could break something that seemed flat-out indestructible. Some people suspect that Steve Rodgers is going to die, there're rumors that Sebastian Stan will take up the role of Captian America in Captain America: the Civil war, and, according to what I have read, the comics state that Bucky took the Captain's place after he thought he died. So here's my theory: it's going to seem as if Steve dies in Age of Ultron, Bucky is going to take his place in the Civil War, and he's eventually going to find out that Steve is actually alive because we all know how Marvel likes to make it seem as if their characters die, but spontaneously resurrects them.

With Robert Downy Jr.'s questionable contract and all (I know there are reports hell do a third on but that could be a cover)But I doubt captain america will die. Thanos did break his shield so maybe that's why we saw the broken shield but that wasn't until Thanos had control of the infinity gauntlet. The hulk, i still believe is "immortal" for now. and honestly i could care less about hawkeye and Romanov. Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
Ok, I'm going to see if I can guess the plots of this movie just using my knowledge of the previous films, the comic books, and this trailer. None of this is coming from a reliable source; I can easily be wrong.

Ultron/Avengers plot- Tony tries to make a system that can protect the universe without the Avengers needing to directly interact (maybe he collaborates with Hank Pym). Needless to say it screws up and now we have Ultron. Ultron screws with J.A.R.V.I.S. (turning him into Vision) and begins to manufacture an army of 'droids in order to eradicate humanity. J.A.R.V.I.S./Vision is whats controlling the Hulkbuster armor, not Tony. Vision either realizes that what he is doing is wrong or gets fixed by Tony, so they can now defeat Ultron.

Hulk/Black Widow plot- Once again, Hulk is seen as a menace and is being hunted by the government, hence the weird tanks in the woods scene in the trailer. A strange love triangle between Black Widow, Bruce Banner, and Hulk comes into play, most likely Bruce and Natasha get a thing going and Natasha tries to see Bruce in Hulk.

Thor plot- SOMEHOW the Infinity Gauntlet will come into play in this movie, probably by some convenient plot device that allows Thanos to get it for Avengers 3.

Iron Man plot- Tony becomes more cynical after the Ultron thing happens, and tries to be all pacifistic again, only to break out the armor again during Avengers 3.

Captain America plot- no reasonable guesses, most likely not influencing the plot heavily or adding to his tale in any meaningful way. 

Hawkeye plot- see Captain America

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
Alright kids, here are my predictions for Age of Ultron based on the trailer. Again, this is all theoretical.

Also Spoiler alert! Don't read if you aren't up to date with Ultron news.

1. Early in the story, Bruce banner is possessed by the Scarlet Witch, which turns the Hulk on the Avengers. This makes Banner feel guilt and gives for the destruction he's caused and makes him realize no one is safe.
2. While the Avengers are in Johannesburg, Black Panther will be introduced.
3. Ultron will be able to lock into any technology on Earth, making him unstoppable. In order to get rid of Ultron, they have to launch him into orbit.
4. Bruce will sacrifice himself to stop Ultron [This is where the redemption from earlier comes in].
5. Banner going into orbit can either mean Planet Hulk[squeal], or create the bridge that will lead to a Guardians of the Galaxy/Avengers crossover.
6. Stark will feel guilt that his creation sent one of his best friends into space, prompting him to repent. This will lead to the " Superhuman Registration Act", which will lead to Civil War in Captain America 3.

That's it so far... What are your thoughts?

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
The design and the teaser leads me to believe that Tony built this thing to be the AI head over some robot-drone guardian program.

See, I'm guessing Tony wants to quit being Iron Man.  He's had enough.  Nearly lost his woman a few times, so that's it, enough.  

So, he designs these Iron Man drones...maybe liking Ivan Vanko's idea from IM2...Naturally, they do fantastic at first, so Tony's ecstatic.  At first.  

But he's Tony Stark, so 'fantastic' isn't good enough.  So, rather than let a version of his Jarvis AI run the drones, he makes a mental copy of 'himself.'  Because only Tony Stark's brilliant mind would be good enough for Tony Stark's purposes.  

He installs this Tony-AI into the drone program and it works even 'better' and 'now', he's satisfied.

What he doesn't know, what no one knows is that the Hydra program from The Winter Soldier is still active out there and it gets into the Tony-AI.  Infects it, changes its mentality.  

Remember what the algorithm does: Assesses threats.  And so it does, and it assesses that the world is 'full' of threats to peace and tranquility.  

The brilliance of Tony Stark in a state-of-the-art war machine drone, with the cold logic of the Hydra algorithm directing its actions.  

OR


My other take is that the AI, like I said before, is based on Tony's mind. So it starts working well. 

BUT, as we all know, Tony is not a perfect ball of morality and sunshine. He has a dark side. His dark side is kept at bay by the support of Pepper and his team. And probably a few martinis here and there.

The AI doesn't have that, Tony can't program perfect empathy into an aritificial construct. So that dark, calculating, weapon making side of Tony becomes more and more prominent in this AI. This AI starts to learn, and adapt. It watches countless drones that it controls fly across the planet, seeing every dispicable, horrid act humanity is capable of without having the human perspective of, "Humans can become better creatures". This leads it to realize that in order to stop the disease that is humanity, it must get rid of it. 

While it's master and his masters friends are up a few floors drinking and dicking around, he decides to take matters into his own hands. He uploads himself into a wrecked Iron Drone that is in Tony's lab. He then joins his master in the party room and announces his new found freedom by claiming he has cut the strings that bound him to Tony. 

Then all Iron Drone hell breaks loose.

I feel by making Ultron a clone of Tony's mind, it not only adds a new twist  to the whole "AI hates humanity" trope, but it also forces Tony to realize that the concept of hating humanity was inside him all along. It would add this tremendous weight to his shoulders knowing not only did he make this cold, unfeeling monster that almost destroyed humanity, but that that monster exists inside himself as well. All the pain and destruction it caused was also caused by him. ﻿
FULL CREDIT GOES TO REDDIT USER: Infernalism and Soundslikecoffee﻿

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
Just gonna clarify some things.

Stop complaining: Joss Whedon's plan is to make each Marvel movie darker and more serious and mature as the Phases progress. So expect this one to have a darker theme than the previous Marvel movies.

Quicksilver: There's a reason they didn't use X-Men's Quicksilver and that's 'cause of character property rights. And to avoid character collision between X-Men's Quicksilver and Avengers' Quicksilver, they cast another actor and are gonna leave out details about him like 'who's his father?' who happens to be Magneto.

Hulkbuster: That's the thing Hulk battles with in some of the scenes. That large and fat suit Tony uses. According to sources also, it's  he first scene they filmed on set so its pretty much a key scene or something major. Also shows that falling bricks from the Bruce/Tony Science Bromance because thing is, Tony knows how dangerous of a threat Bruce is that he even created a suit about twice as big as Hulk to fight him if that time comes, which unfortunately does.

Ultron: The reason why he sounds like that is because Joss Whedon wanted his voice to not be robotic but human-like to show what horror Tony had truly created and what Ultron is capable of. Also, a key point to his god complex.

Cap's broken shield: If you went to the Comic Con earlier this year and saw the teaser trailer they showed there, which is a different one from this, the scene where Cap's broken shield is shown to be some sort of illusion/dream Tony has because in that scene, Tony is standing in front of all his team mates' corpses and that included Cap and his broken shield. Don't worry too much. Plus, Chris Evans has a 6-picture contract and if I'm right, this is just his 4th movie.

Thanos: He's gonna appear in Phase Three, just not in Phase Two. Why? The studio thought it to be a bad idea for having two aliens as consecutive villains in consecutive films. Remember Loki being the bad guy in Avengers? If Thanos was the bad guy in this one... well, they it was just plain stupid.

Ultron creator: They're diverging from the comics at this point because a source said that it was not Hank Pym who creates Ultron but Tony Stark himself in the film series.

Anymore questions?

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
Looks so good! Was gonna see it anyway, but showed enough to get me super-excited. I'm a comic nerd, Marvel, DC, Dark Horse, Image, etc... gotta say Marvel knows what to do (as far as movies). DC has amazing animated movies/series (Young Justice, Flashpoint Paradox, Dark Knight Returns, etc), but Marvel movies have all been pretty good, so I'm in.

Sorry to say it, but Nolan Trilogy is over-rated. I think of it as Nolan's version of Batman, just like there was Burton, Schumacher, and '66 Batman, It's nothing like the comic Batman. Closest on-screen to comic was TAS. My fave was Begins, cause it felt the closest and was a "realistic" version, tho still some flaws (League of Assassins never trained Bruce). And although I do enjoy Dark Knight and somewhat Rises, they're nothing like the comic versions. Ledger's Joker is memorable and brilliant, but his character is nothing like the Joker in comics, more like the Riddler, planning everything down to the second (completely contradictory to what he says to Dent in hospital). Joker should've been more like Bane in Rises (anarchy throughout city w/o cops). & Bane is nothing like in the comics, South American mercenary hooked on Venom drug (super steroids). Also plot-holes galore in last two, so ridiculous, especially since they're trying to be smart crime dramas, but they're clearly not.

"A ninth incarnation of Ultron arose when Tony Stark rebuilt the robot, acting on a post-hypnotic command Ultron had given him long before, but the Avengers fought the robot and Hawkeye knocked Ultron into a vat of molten Adamantium, which cooled into an unbreakable prison. Cybernetically manipulating Jocasta, Ultron compelled her to rebuild him as the tenth Ultron, after which he began creating more Ultron models to serve as worker drones and backup bodies for himself. He was opposed by the Thing, Jocasta and her new robotic admirer, Machine Man. During the fight, Jocasta sacrificed herself trying to destroy Ultron, but it was Machine Man who finally deactivated Ultron by reaching down his throat and wrecking his internal mechanisms."

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
Ok, to everyone in the comments complaining about how awful the movie will be:
*It's. A. Trailer.* A teaser trailer no less. The whole point of it is to show you a tiny glimpse of what is to come, and no one knows anything about the plot other than "Ultron turns evil and attempts to wipe out Earth's human population". So you can start complaining when the movie actually does come out — next year.
Of course, by then everyone else won't care in the slightest, so... maybe you shouldn't be complaining about a movie.

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
This trailer is really incredible, I wouldn't have thought using a song from Pinocchio would ever work, but it's so haunting. Hats off to the guys who came up with the idea!

On a more serious note, as much as I love the trailer, it just hammers home the point that Iron Man 3 is made completely pointless and irrelevant. Even though we don't see it up close, you can see the arc reactor in the Hulkbuster suit, so I assume he's using an arc reactor again. Regardless, he's building and using Iron Man suits again, even after saying he wouldn't. How do you guys think that will work?

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment: Man of Steele superman blows up a ship full of Krypton babies. Max Landis makes such good points about that movie. I think the problem with the Nolan films was that Batmans motives for why he's batman change so drastically between each film. His reasoning behind his actions also come across as psychotic he as a character is all over the place from film to film. He has no natural progressive story as a character. Oh I don't want people helping me in dark knight because they lack training and my tech and gear and use guns. In rises he gives the mantle to a rookie cop who uses guns, has no training or anything it just makes doesn't make sense. Niether does his statement to Gordon in the end of rises, he tells him anyone could be Batman that's what its all about, that's what Batman has always been about but that contradicts everything that happens in dark knight. Its all just a incoherent mess. The Nolan movies look nice and are shot nice but they depict a Batman who is scitso and crazy and a quiter. Batman would never quit being Batman EVER the fact that he gave his mantle to rookie cop goes against everything Batman represents.  Plus according to the TIMELINE of the movies between Dark Knight and Begins he's only been Batman for what? 6 maybe 7 months. And he wants to quit already!? All for Rachel! Or how how he's willing to just erase all of catwomans past and run away with her and fake his death and NOT TELL ALFRED AT ALL! He's almost as vindictive and evil as peter parker is by the end of Amazing Spiderman 1. I grew to despise Batman  by the end of rises. Say what you want about Burton's batman movies but at least he wasnt a whiny quiter with crazy back and forth motives. Sure he killed dudes but Burton's batman was very cut and dry he worked. And in M.O.S superman is just a killing machine raised by pa Kent who he let die. Lol. Its as if DC doesn't hire writers who even bother to read the comics.

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
Concerning Ultron and the "strings"...
Ultimately Ulton's purpose is the safety and protection of the world, he arrives at the ultimate conclusion that humanity is the single greatest threat to the world (that he is aware of, mind you), and thus proceeds to work towards the logical goal, the extermination of humanity.

The song works splendidly for a variety of reasons: first note how all the Avengers are standing or rather, watching from an elevated platform upon Ultron's little "show" with the other robot/suit.

Similar to a certain little living puppet... 

The song makes reference not only to Ultron's growth into a "real boy" free of Stark's control, but it's lyrics also to Ultron's belief that if the Avengers were truly committed, solely, to the protection of the planet, they too would work against humanity, that they wouldn't simply be a "show" in the grand scheme of things, accomplishing nothing of substance.

Why don't they?

Because they're "tangled". Constrained by their morals, their hearts, their doubts, their fears, their love, their joy. To Ultron, there is only the goal. In a sense he is free, but also still very much constrained by his singularity of focus.

Comment: I dont see Thanos and the Avengers facing off anytime soon, and if they do, it just CAN NOT BE without the likes of Cyclops, Spiderman, Wolverine, Silver Surfer. How could you not hope to see Nebula bash Spiderman's head into the ground, or rip off Ironman's head for that matter, or watch Cyclops suffocate in a glass cube, or see Wolverine's adamantium bones turned into rubber. Silver Surfer with perhaps the most crucial of appearances cant be excluded at all. This might take 5 Avenger movies just to get all the pieces in place and it would be a DAMN SHAME if we never see this because of STUDIO RIGHTS. They shouldnt be greedy when they are BOTH bound to make a truck load of money as it will be the BIGGEST Marvel mash up EVER plus it finally ends the series and opens the doors for future titles like A VS X, Dark Avengers, House of M, Civil War, Planet Hulk, World War Hulk, Secret Wars, Etc...

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
I hope the sound quality to Ultron is better in final film. It sounds Garbled and awful, like Hardy's Bane. Spader is a charismatic actor with a low, graveled voice. You have to hit the pitches right or it sounds like feedback.

It looks like some elements of this movie will be lead ins to Captain America 3: Civil War. Should be interesting. And I appreciate that Vision was left out of the trailer. We know too much already I think.

And there is no reason for DC/Marvel love/hate anymore. This is ridiculous banter. DC is catching up to the reinvention that Marvel products started back with Blade in the theaters. It was an independent project then, but Blade set the standard for comic involvement in cinema in the next century for all of these comic companies.

If you want to match up the two companies, both have had ups and downs in their pics and now Marvel has hit their stride with their major movie franchises (Iron Man, Thor & Captain America) and it is picking up steam with SHIELD and perhaps will generate a new market with Netflix's "Marvel Knights" features. DC, with any luck will come into its own with "Dawn of Justice" having made stellar numbers with the "Dark Knight" franchise and the "Man of Steel" but was by far the bigger small screen presence with Smallville, however it has had its flops too before striking it big with "Arrow" and "Gotham".

Absurd to get into this Team Marvel v. Team DC sort of thing. I hope for great adaptations from both companies because I grew up with both.

Besides, I want to see a conclusion to Hellboy and a revisit to League of Extraordinary Gentlemen. Give me more fringe stuff like "Invincible" or "Savage Dragon".

I mean, The Avengers worked so well because they all had their personality's established in their solo movies, but quick silver, scarlet witch and vision have not. Besides that, you have to progress with the story and establish Ultron as a badass villain!
It worries me, but the trailer makes it look like the greatest thing ever! And i really like the tone of the trailer, a lot darker than the other marvel movie's tones. but then again, the trailer for iron man 3 was dark and that movie was cheesy and comickbooky as hell!

Comment:
Ultron  was created by Roy Thomas and John Buscema and his first adventure was in Avengers # 54 July 1968. 

The Ultron robot was a project of Dr. Henry Pym (who at the time attended the Avengers as Ant-Man). Ultron's body consists of a variation of Adamantium, metal fictional Marvel Universe virtually indestructible. 

Ultron rebelled against the creator and hypnotized Hulk to attack the Avengers, being given as destroyed in the ensuing fight. After that your program spent perfecting his metal body, which already had several versions. 

Ultron is notable for having created two beings who became powerful Avengers: Vision, a copy of the android body that made the Original Human Torch. And Jocasta, Ultron a female version of himself.

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
I have strong feeling this movie will be epic on so many levels. I really enjoyed Ultron storylines in comics (i mean i loved but hated him as villain), though first encounter came to suprisingly anti-climatic solution.
Oh and geek in me and huge Stargate franchise fan loves to see James Spader (known to SG fans as Daniel Jackson from 1994 movie) is playing Ultron. from geek to villain
(warning, possible spoilers ahead of previous marvel movies and comics, so read at your own risk)
i am geniuenly interested, how many connections they plan to make with actual comics. I mean, all we know to date is that Ultron is made by Iron man, not by Hank Pym (also known as Goliath at time of Ultron 1 creation, other more famous aliases include ant-man, giant-man, yellowjacket). I mean Pym (or Janet "winsome wasp" van Dyne) doesnt apparently appear here, which is actually bit sad, but then again, 2 huge brains in same movie (Stark and Pym) would probably be not so good idea, especially as Pym adds more drama. Still, does Stark uses his brainwaves (as Pym did) to map Ultron's brain?
Speaking of changes in roster, compared to first encounter with Ultron (Ultron-5) in comics, Hulk is on roster. Bruce Banner's hulk (i.e not counting Red hulk) was part of avengers only for 3 first issues for years and also Black widow is in team.
What makes this avengers more interesting is that S.H.I.E.L.D disbanded in Captain America: The winter soldier, which should mean that Avengers are now their own team rather than goverment agency, which is quite interesting as in comics it was other way around: Avengers came together after defeating Loki and they were basically independent for certain time.
And now we reach probably one of most interesting parts for me personally- Vision. In comics, Vision was made from body of original Human Torch (not to be confused with Jhonny Storm- Fantastic Four's human torch)- the one that was android. Brain waves used to make Vision's mind were the ones of Simon Williams, power man, who was made as weapon by masters of evil (baron Zemo, enchantress and executioner (latter 2 are asgardians)) to kill avengers, but he had last minute change of heart and saved avengers and died in progress. he was later revived though.
Question here is that since neither android human torch or power man arent even hinted to exist in marvel cinematic universe as of now and if they arent hinted in movie, yet Vision would act same as in comics i.e join avengers against Ultron, it wouldnt be good if it isnt replaced with anything similar. I mean reason why Vision turned to its apparent creator, Ultron (whom he believed created him) was that Vision had brain patterns of power man and some leftover ones of android human torch.
Its also interesting to think wheter or not will Scarlet witch and Vision fall in love in cinematic universe too. descriptions also hint that we may see early hints of Scarlet Witch losing her mind before Avengers disassembled equivelant

In any case, this movie will be interesting.

If anyone cared to read such a long post, then please, discuss with me what do you think

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
Ultron foi criado por Roy Thomas e John Buscema e sua primeira aventura foi em Avengers # 54 de julho de 1968.

O robô Ultron foi um projeto do Dr. Henry Pym (que na época participava dos Vingadores como Homem-Formiga). O corpo de Ultron é constituído de uma variação de Adamantium, metal fictício do Universo Marvel praticamente indestrutivel.

Ultron rebelou-se contra o criador e hipnotizou Hulk para atacar os Vingadores, sendo dado como destruído na luta que se seguiu. Depois disso seu programa passou a aperfeiçoar seu corpo de metal, que já teve várias versões.

Ultron é notável por ter criado dois seres que se tornaram poderosos Vingadores: o Visão, de uma cópia que fez do corpo andróide do Tocha Humana Original. E Jocasta, uma versão fêmea do próprio Ultron.

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
A couple of things to point out in this trailer

#1 - at 0:16 Quicksilver and Scarlet Witch screaming in the crowd

#2 - at 0:37 The avengers in the Avengers tower along with 2 unknown burnette women.  Possibly Maria Hill? Or two women Tony invited just because.... well he's Tony Stark (assuming he broke up with Pepper.......hopefully).

#3 - at 1:02 Possibly Ultron's lair where he upgrades himself?

#4 - at 1:06  Two types of Ultron bots.  Ones with jetpacks, and ones without.... could there be more types? 

#5 at 1:23 Pieces of armor flying at Iron Man similar to his Mark 48 in Iron Man 3.  Also arc reactors on his knees.  Maybe the suit is a combination of multiple suits?  Or simple needs more power to take on the Hulk?

#6 at 1:31 looks a lot like it could be a flash-back sequince with Cap in the 1940's

#7 at 1:33 you can see actor Andy Serkis who is rumored to be playing Ulysses Klaw AKA The Klaw, one of Black Panther's major villains!!!  

#8 at 1:36 ballerinas? Could it be a flash-back for Black Widow?

#9 at 1:39 The shot of Thor grabbing Tony is actually two different scenes.  Note Thor's costume change from him approaching, what we thought was Tony, to him actually grabbing Tony.  Also the two shots are in two different rooms, the second most likely being Avengers tower (windows in the back)

#10 at 1:41 is Hulk getting smarter?  Hulk throws a car, destracting Iron Man and leaving him wide open for Hulk's punch.  Smart move from a bruting hulk huh? (pun intended)

#11 at 1:53 judging by the cracks in the middle of Cap's shield and spreading outwards suggest it was punched?  Cap's shield is stated to be made of vibranium and is indestructible.  So we can assume that the only thing that can damage his shield is..... more vibranium?  The only place you can find more vibranium is in Wakanda, Africa; home of the Black Panther.  

So we got:
Cap's broken shield needing a repair, rumors of The Klaw making an appearance, movie scenes being shot in Africa, and Ultron beings known to upgrade himself with an Adamantium body, another indestructible metal in the comics but cant be used in this movie due to legal rights (thanks Fox).  So Ultron will most likely be coated in vibranium instead...... All this adds up to some major ground work being down for the Black Panther movie!  Maybe we'll get an actual appearance?  Maybe an after credits scene? Who knows....

#12 And FINALLY at 1:56 Ultron looking slightly more human than in the comics, with the Transformer like eyes, and a moving mouth, we can conclude that this villain looks AWESOME and very intimidating...

I cant WAIT for this movie, who's with me?

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
WOW,there are some SUPER uneducated people here,so let's clear some stuff up (even though it's public record)
1.James Spader voices and provided some movements for Ultron,film is in post production,so his voice will most likely be tweaked (even though I loved it,)the Pinocchio reference points to the fact that Ultron is part human in a sense due to his programming (which disgusts him) and is no longer "attached to" or controlled by Stark
2.Not only was Quicksilver announced for Avengers:AOU WELL before X-Men:DOFP (it's generally thought that Fox threw a fit at the fact that Disney were able to use him),but Quicksilver's 1st appearence was in The Avengers as was Scarlet Witch,and it wasn't til much later that they were revealed as Mutants
3.this whole "That looks like crap cause I love DC" argument is childish,and in my honest opinion an affront to what you claim to be (if you claim to be a comic book fan that is),If you are a comic book fan then it is NOT a competition,you either love good stories (Every company has some),or you don't and you just jumped on the bandwagon when Hollywood noticed that these films can make money,in which case commenting on the trailer of the follow up to the most successful CBM ever made is probably not the place for you.

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
What do you suppose the "main" Ultron will be made of? My guess is Vibranium. He's been made out of pretty much every fictional and real metal imaginable at one point or another.

Yes, Adamantium is the most common, but it hasn't been mentioned at all in this movie universe. Introducing a new concept now (especially in the midst of all the other things they're introducing as well) just seems unnecessary when they could just as easily do Vibrainum. Besides, Vibranium could arguably be an even bigger threat than Adamantium. At least he couldn't absorb energy with Adamantium.

Also, Adamantium is closely tied to the X-Men franchise. Yes, it appears in other comic books, but not nearly as often as X-Men. I wouldn't be surprised if they don't have the rights to use Adamantium.

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment: Looks like our worst (or best for some people) thoughts are confirming. Ultron, an android created by Stark Industries goes out of control and develops a God complex and wants to exterminate the human civilization. The conflict with Ultron leaves Tony Stark (slated to appear in Captain America 3 - May 2016) with a moral impact that makes him to create a federal law who will regulate individuals with super powers beacuse of Quicksilver and Scarlet Witch. In the comics, it's called "Civil War" storyline, and appears that events between Age of Ultron and Cap 3 are leading to this. Stark is pro-registration and Rogers not.

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
My theory about Ultron's and Hank Pym's origin:
After creating Ultron, Hank Pym showed the A.I. multiple Disney films (his personal favorite being Pinocchio) in hopes it would teach Ultron about humanity and give it a sense of emotions. However, Ultron interpreted them far differently, seeing the quote "I have no strings and now I'm free" as disregarding all morals and others (the strings) to achieve a free world. When Ultron did something truly horrible, Pym felt responsible and ashamed for his actions; thus he shut down Ultron before going into hiding in a desolate location (0:48). Now, after Tony Stark accidentally reawakens Ultron (0:31), the A.I. begins to eradicate the human species to achieve a free world, leaving the Avengers to search for Pym, hoping he has the answer on how to defeat Ultron. 
So, what do you guys think?

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment: !SPOILERS! Ultron's outer armor is usually composed primarily of adamantium, which is almost completely impervious to damage (the first use of the term "adamantium" in Marvel Comics was made in reference to Ultron in Avengers #66, published in July 1969). Most Ultron units are powered by a small internal nuclear furnace and incorporate a "program transmitter" which can beam part or all of Ultron's memory/personality system into other computer systems or duplicate robotic bodies. Ultron can also control other machines remotely. Ultron has occasionally reformed itself with a humanoid appearance above the waist and the appearance of a complex machine, including tractor beam apparatus for flight, below the waist. A later Ultron model developed hive-mind technology, allowing it to animate and control hundreds of other Ultron bodies simultaneously,although only the 'prime' Ultron was composed of adamantium while others were made of steel or secondary adamantium due to the lack of resources to give all the Ultrons adamantium bodies.Ultron also uses an internal molecular rearranger that renders the adamantium components of its workings more malleable and so have the ability to restructure his physical form. What circuitry Ultron has is carefully shielded to protect from damage, although the Scarlet Witch is capable of causing malfunctions with her hex power, Johnny Storm, using his nova burst, managed to damage Ultron's internal circuits while his outer armor remained intact,[47] and Wonder Man was once able to destroy an Ultron by throwing it so hard its internal systems were damaged

The problem with me is that I consider most of MARVEL trailers as being absolutely brilliant and infinitely amazing; and the Avengers' ones seem "only" very good. But just to set things straight, I thought the exact same thing about the first movie. I super-loved the first Avengers movie, but I found the trailer looking really average. So I hope it's just the same thing with this one and that I'll adore it once I see it in theaters!

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
Marvel has to be really, really careful, how far their going to push this entire franchise thing. You simply can't constantly have such a high output on individual movies, and keep up the quality.
Even worse, you can't keep up a coherent continuity... and in the newer movies, we've already seen first problems in regards of consistency to the entire canon popping up.
I really hope that they won't fall into the same trap as pretty much all larger franchises eventually have fallen into. Because so far, they did a much better job, than any of us could have had expected.

That said:
This trailer looks awesome! And as cynical as I am towards the entire franchise-thing that has more and more become the rule for big blockbuster-movies, I can't deny that this trailer makes me really excited!
